If it was a cli model:

input.py should only be collecting user input from the web form and writing to gmap.json

INPUT.PY [DESTINATION][START_LOCATION][[START_TIME][START_DAY]][[ARRIVE_BY_TIME][ARRIVE_BY_DAY][CITY="STRING"][LAST][CODE="STRING"][MODE="STRING"]

where: 

input.py default is: input.py "mydestination" 

the next step would be:

input.py "mydestination + mystartlocation" i.e + = "from"

input.py "mydestination + mystartlocation" [LAST]

and so on with the flags


[CITY="mycity"] is a standalone query. No direction logic required. Just writes to gmap.json

[MODE="mymode"] iis a standalone query. No direction logic required. Just writes to gmap.json

CODE denotes a string and/or a google placeID




